sort of, but not really. accessories like the beanies, crowns, and glasses are a seperate mesh from the body of the character itself, but still bound to the movement of a bone from the rig i make in blender. when i import a character + the accessories attached to them into the game engine, these collection of meshes are still seperate objects; i can make ERQ's crown invisible or outright delete it during gameplay and she'll still remain functional. what i havent tried was adding a replacement mesh during gameplay, like a helment instead of a crown in real-time.
